<br>
Yes, true, only now it's just Sony, and a nearly everyone that was originally part of everquest as Verant is gone. And while some at Sony may think 6 wizards taking down a Kunark dragon was ok, 12, 18, 24 or however many wizards, taking down gods was not a good thing. <br>
<br>
I'm sure manaburn teams would have PLd wizards up and full of AA's and then start auctioning of raids to get flagged. If Manaburn hadn't been nerfed, guilds would have  been in the Plane of Time in half of the time it took. <br>
<br>
As for making some mobs able to resist Manaburn, that wasn't going to happen, because the idea behind it was that it was a mob couldn't resist it. If new mobs suddenly had started resisting Manaburn, there would have been a huge outcry of unfair. <br>
<br>
To also be fair, blame goes to Verant too. The always seemed to think in terms of &quot;This is the ultimate expression of this classes powers.&quot; Which is why you get clerics that can Complete heal for 10k at level 39, when no one at level 39 could even dream (even to this day) of having 10K hit points. Even with PoP where the cap on warriors HPs was raised to 12k, many level 65 warriors only come close to having 10k hps. Don't get me wrong, I'm not calling for a cleric nerf. But lowering CH from 10k to 7.5 hardly hurt them. <br>
<br>
Verant seemed to believe in the carrot before the donkey way of getting characters to play. The good rewards come when you reach the top level for your class. The best spells, mobs drop the best equipment. When they did come out with expansions, it was the same thing. The better gear is in the new expansion, to get you to go there. <br>
<br>
Sony thinks of this as a business, and a cash cow, and rightly so. I have no problem with them thinking like that. It's a business and a form of entertainment. There is no humanitarian reason for them to do this. And because they are thinking that this is a business, they are looking down the road. That is why there are all these new dungeons, and expansions, in the last year. You need product to keep a publics interest. And, unlike Verant, they seem to be interested in actually fixing things. Sure, some of those were doors. But Verant always came across as, &quot;Oh Well&quot;. <br>
<br>
Still, with as gimped manaburn is now, we really need something new. Or at least, a partial return of how it used to be.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=faramir42>Faramir42</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/03 6:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Remember Manaburn?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Please stop repeating the crap that low level bards were brainwashed into believing.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
