<br>
If the argument is that wizards can manaburn team down dragons.   Today, high level necromancers can SOLO kunark dragons.    Only one I have not heard of soloed is Gore.   So that whole line of argument is moot.<br>
<br>
What is sad is that wizards should beyond a shadow of a doubt rule in burst DPS.   Manaburn is inline with this intent.  Wizards at near full mana can use manaburn for 9492 damage cap with no other wizard able to use it on a given mob for 1 minute.   Yet lifeburn uses no mana and is continually used on most large encounters by necromancers.  Similar to HT with 6K+ damage per use.   I see SKs using HT during most major encounters also.   Also, there is does not seem to be the one minute stacking logic built in either.<br>
<br>
Given the current state of Lifeburn/HT and the fact that Kunark dragons are now soloed,  and finally wizards should lead all other classes in burst damage, manaburn needs a great deal of its applicability restored.<br>
<br>
At a minimum, the mana useage of this should be greatly lowered so that its cost is inline with the lifeburn/HT counter parts.   Keep in mind that both of these classes can easily FD off any risk of its uses too.  <br>
<br>
-- If crit is not restored to manaburn and the damage cap remains -- cost of mana should be zero.  Given the relative state of Lifeburn/HT I believe this is justified.<br>
-- If crit is restored and damage cap remains -- manaburn should cost mana at a 4 dmg/ 1 mana ratio.   This would cost the wizard about 2400 mana at the current damage cap.   So not an insignificat cost at all.  If the dmg/mana ratio were worsed -- how would it be inline with the lifeburn/HT counterparts?<br>
-- If the crit is restored and the damage cap goes -- It should use all mana.<br>
<br>
All of the above proposals leave the 1 minute restriction in place which does not exist for either the lifeburn/HT counter parts.  Given that wizards should be masters of burst damage -- what would be wrong with this?<br>
<br>
