<br>
That's kind of like deciding to beat your kid unconscious because he'll cry if you tell him to go sit in a corner.<br>
<br>
The problem with wizards is that we are smarter and more organized than most other classes.  The only way to counter the superiority of the wizard players is to unfairly weaken our class and limit the options available to us, thus removing our threat.<br>
<br>
If you think I'm wrong, ask yourself if manaburn was made to stack again, would wizards be killing Kunark dragons again? Yes? Then why aren't other classes who have that power to do the same, organizing kill groups?<br>
<br>
Wizards have been reduced to nothing more than player controlled DoTs.  All our other abilities have been slowly destroyed over the past expansions.<br>
<br>
When was the last time you pulled a mob, I was the main puller for my guild all the way through ToV until they nerfed Eye of Zomm.  How about port spells, I don't think I've cast anything other than teleport/exodus/abscond for months... PBAE? Quad Kiting? Roots? Snares? Stuns? Rains? Lures?<br>
<br>
Maybe some people still find usefulness in these spells, but you can't deny that they've lost a lot of their former glory.  Has any other class lost so much, and gained so little?<br>
<br>
